threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, No line numbers, No symbols, Large address aware, No debug

attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64 (stripped to external PDB), for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious loader that establishes a backdoor. It creates a named pipe with a deceptive name, `\\.\pipe\MSSE-%d-server`, to receive a payload. The received code is then XOR-decoded, its memory permissions are changed to executable using `VirtualProtect`, and it is executed in a new thread. This is a classic pattern for downloading and running a second-stage payload.
